Note: Pursuant to direction from the Supreme Court opinions will not be published in the following seventeen (17) habeas corpus cases. Rule 32 (k), Supreme Court Rules.

29920. NEAL v. HOPPER. Decided September 2, 1975. James Oliver Neal, pro se.

The trial court did not err in remanding the appellant to custody.

Judgment affirmed.

All the Justices concur, except Gunter and Ingram, JJ., who concur in the judgment only. Hill, J., disqualified. *776Arthur K. Bolton, Attorney General, for appellee.
